    {
      "block_type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. Oil pump."
    },
    {
      "block_type": "prose",
      "text": "The oil pump is driven by the engine via a shaft passing through the primary pulley. The pump is of the external gear type. As well as providing line pressure to operate the control valve, the pump also lubricates the drive belt by spraying oil (at high pressure) directly on to it. The pulley ratio sensor is also lubricated in the same manner.",
      "style": "normal"
    },
